The paper proposes a deep learning approach for anomaly detection, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on developing deep structured energy-based models (DSEBMs) for different types of data, such as static, sequential, and spatial data. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and cryptography and security (cs.CR), as these sub-categories are closely related to the topic of anomaly detection and deep learning.
